          "text": "Base directory for this skill: /Users/andrew.balmer/.claude/plugins/cache/klaviyo-plugins/mage/2.6.3/skills/pr-draft\n\n# PR Draft\n\nFull review→fix→draft PR workflow. Orchestrate code review, implement fixes, and create or update high-quality draft pull requests.\n\nTake changes from the current branch and shepherd them to a draft PR by:\n1. Gathering context (repo conventions, existing PR, templates)\n2. Running code review via `reviewer` agent/skill from this plugin in a clean context\n3. Prioritize and implementing fixes for issues found, treat nitpicks with skepticism\n4. Iterating until quality is acceptable\n5. Resolving any conflicts with the base branch\n6. Creating a new draft PR or updating the existing one\n\n**Max iterations:** Use `` if provided, otherwise default to 2. If 0, skip the review and go to Phase 4 and 5\n\n## Phase 1: Context Gathering\n\n1. **Read repository context:**\n   - Read `AGENTS.md` at repo root (fall back to `CLAUDE.md` if absent)\n   - Note build commands, test commands, and project-specific conventions\n\n2. **Identify the repository and branch:**\n   ```bash\n   git branch --show-current\n   git remote -v\n   ```\n\n3. **Check for an existing PR on this branch:**\n   ```bash\n   gh pr view --json number,title,body,url,state,baseRefName 2>/dev/null\n   ```\n   - If a PR exists: **update mode**. Record the PR number, URL, current title, body, and base branch.\n   - If no PR exists: **create mode**.\n\n4. **Find the PR template:**\n   - Check `.github/PULL_REQUEST_TEMPLATE.md`\n   - Check `.github/PULL_REQUEST_TEMPLATE/` directory\n   - If no template exists, use Summary / Changes / Testing sections\n\n5. **Determine the base branch:**\n   - **Update mode:** Use the base branch from the existing PR\n   - **Create mode:** Check the current branch name first:\n     - `rel/*`, `ci/*`, or `docs/*` branches → target `master` directly, no confirmation needed\n     - All other branches (`feat/*`, `{initials}/*`, hotfixes, etc.) → suggest `master` as the default, then **ask the user**:\n       > \"This branch can't merge directly into `master` — you'll need to target a `rel/*` branch (or another intermediate branch). What branch should this PR open against? (Default: `master` if you want to set that up later)\"\n     - List available remote release branches for reference: `git branch -r | grep rel/`\n     - If the user's desired target branch doesn't exist yet, offer to create it now (`git push origin HEAD:refs/heads/<branch-name>`) or proceed with `master` as a placeholder and retarget later\n   - **Do not silently open against `master`** for non-`rel/ci/docs` branches — a required status check will block the merge and the CI bot will post a correction comment on the PR\n\n## Phase 2: Review Loop\n\n**Maximum iterations as configured above.** Each iteration:\n\n1. **Invoke the Reviewer:**\n\n   Use the Task tool to launch the `reviewer` agent:\n   ```\n   Task(subagent_type=\"reviewer\", prompt=\"Review all changes on this branch compared to <base-branch>. Provide findings categorized as High, Medium, Low, or Nit. If a PR exists, include unresolved reviewer feedback.\")\n   ```\n\n   **Context management:**\n   - **Fresh context (default):** After implementing fixes. The reviewer sees the code fresh.\n   - **Resume previous reviewer:** Only when actively debugging a tricky issue and need continuity.\n\n2. **Analyze findings:**\n   - **Unresolved PR Feedback**: Issues from human reviewers — treat as High severity\n   - **High**: Bugs, security issues, breaking changes — MUST fix\n   - **Medium**: Inconsistencies, missing tests, performance — SHOULD fix\n   - **Low/Nit**: Nice-to-haves, cosmetic — MAY fix, use judgement\n\n3. **Triage unresolved PR threads:**\n   When the reviewer surfaces **Unresolved PR Feedback**, apply the triage protocol from `review-playbook.md` (in the grimoire directory). The reviewer identifies the threads; the playbook guides how to handle them — assess